19/03/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- During a meeting Monday (17 March), Defence Secretary Donald Rumsfeld assured his Macedonian counterpart, Vlado Buckovski, that Washington would not allow rebel or extremist groups to destabilise Macedonia.
He added that the United States will not withdraw from the Balkans.
Rumsfeld also thanked Buckovski for supporting global efforts against terrorism and the coalition against Iraq.
Noting progress in implementing the Ohrid peace accord and in military reforms, Rumsfeld said Washington would try to help accelerate Macedonia's accession to NATO.
In other news, the government approved Tuesday a project aimed at controlling light weapons in the country.
The project, organised by the UNDP, is designed to draft national policy on light weapons and a trans-border strategy to combat illegal arms trafficking.Also Tuesday, the government launched debate on an action plan aimed at the equitable representation of minorities in public administration.
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik, MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 19/03/03;
MIA, A1 TV - 18/03/03)
